cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper discusses the challenges and approaches for understanding non-optical remote-sensed images, which involves image processing and analysis. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it requires the development of algorithms and models for image understanding. Additionally, the use of unmanned air vehicles and satellites suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application areas of disaster management, crime, and precision agriculture may also fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR) as they involve visual representation and interpretation of data.
